# Hardening & Violation Resolution Plan

The goal is to achieve a truly Zero Tolerance state in the COE Kernel codebase by addressing all IDE-reported errors, warnings, and informationals.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Improvement Engine

#### [MODIFY] [engine.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/improvement_engine/engine.py)
- Remove unused `List` and `Optional` imports.
- Wrap line 59 to adhere to the 100-character limit.
- Audit imports to ensure they are compatible with the IDE's resolution logic (potentially shifting to relative imports if absolute imports from `core` are causing issues, though first I will check if the root is the issue).

#### [MODIFY] [ci_gate.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/improvement_engine/ci_gate.py)
